HEADWORD: Gaudy
<hw>Gaud"y</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A feast or festival; -- called also
<altname>gaud-day</altname> and <altname>gaudy day</altname>.</def>
<mark>[Oxford Univ.]</mark> <rj><au>Conybeare.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
